06/08/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Supreme Military Council has decided to dismiss 17 army officers, blamed for pro-Islamist activities or breaching army discipline. 
Wrapping up its annual three-day session on Thursday (3 August), the council also decided on the promotions of 32 army generals and admirals, as well 47 lower-ranking officers.
In other news, a Kurdish extremist group calling itself Kurdistan Freedom Falcons (TAK) has claimed responsibility for two bomb blasts in the southern town of Adana on Friday that injured 17 people, including eight police officers. 
TAK is believed to be linked to the terrorist organisation Kurdistan Workers Party. 
(Radikal, Sabah, Zaman - 05/08/06; NTV, AFP, Cihan - 04/08/06)
